methods.name: createTrade

args.name: ipfsHash
args.desc: - IPFS hash of purchase order (legacy field)

args.name: buyerLEI
args.desc: - Buyer's Legal Entity Identifier (full JSON string)

args.name: sellerLEI
args.desc: - Seller's Legal Entity Identifier (full JSON string)

methods.desc:
Create trade with vLEI documents (buyer initiates)

IMPORTANT: This method now accepts vLEI documents with IPFS hashes
- All vLEI JSON objects are stored on-chain in boxes
- IPFS hashes are stored as backup/reference
- Boxes must be included in transaction: trades, metadata, vlei_c, buyer, seller

methods.name: escrowTradeAsFinancier
methods.desc: Escrow trade as financier - third party locks funds (ALGO)

methods.name: escrowTradeAsFinancierWithAsset
methods.desc: Escrow trade as financier - third party locks funds (ASA)

methods.name: executeTrade

args.name: rwaInstrumentLEI_IPFS
args.desc: - IPFS hash for RWA instrument LEI

methods.desc: Execute trade with execution vLEI documents - seller transfers RWA instrument (ALGO)

methods.name: executeTradeWithAsset
methods.desc: Execute trade with execution vLEI documents (ASA version)

methods.name: expireTrade
methods.desc: Expire trade - admin function to cancel and refund
